# Metrics Collection Standards - 2025

Implement comprehensive metrics collection for RED (Rate, Errors, Duration) and USE (Utilization, Saturation, Errors) methodologies.

**Justification:** Metrics provide quantitative insights into system health, performance, and business KPIs enabling proactive issue detection.

## 🎯 Single Responsibility
This rule is ONLY responsible for defining WHAT metrics to collect and HOW to collect them. Not alerting (see alert-definitions) or visualization (see dashboards).

## 📋 Implementation Checklist

### Initial Setup
```markdown
- [ ] Choose metrics library (Prometheus client, OpenTelemetry Metrics)
- [ ] Set up metrics endpoint (/metrics)
- [ ] Configure metric types (Counter, Gauge, Histogram, Summary)
- [ ] Implement RED metrics (Rate, Errors, Duration)
- [ ] Implement USE metrics (Utilization, Saturation, Errors)
- [ ] Add business KPI metrics
- [ ] Configure Prometheus scraping
- [ ] Set up Grafana dashboards
- [ ] Define SLIs and SLOs
- [ ] Configure metric retention
```

## 📊 Metrics Types & Usage

### Counter - Monotonically Increasing Values
```typescript
import { Counter } from 'prom-client';

// Define counters
const httpRequestsTotal = new Counter({
  name: 'http_requests_total',
  help: 'Total number of HTTP requests',
  labelNames: ['method', 'route', 'status_code'],
});

const ordersProcessedTotal = new Counter({
  name: 'orders_processed_total',
  help: 'Total number of orders processed',
  labelNames: ['status', 'payment_method', 'region'],
});

// Usage
httpRequestsTotal.inc({ 
  method: 'POST', 
  route: '/api/orders', 
  status_code: '200' 
});

ordersProcessedTotal.inc({ 
  status: 'completed',
  payment_method: 'credit_card',
  region: 'us-west'
});
```

### Gauge - Values That Go Up and Down
```typescript
import { Gauge } from 'prom-client';

// Define gauges
const activeConnections = new Gauge({
  name: 'active_connections',
  help: 'Number of active connections',
  labelNames: ['service'],
});

const queueDepth = new Gauge({
  name: 'queue_depth',
  help: 'Current depth of the message queue',
  labelNames: ['queue_name', 'priority'],
});

const memoryUsageBytes = new Gauge({
  name: 'memory_usage_bytes',
  help: 'Current memory usage in bytes',
  labelNames: ['type'], // heap, rss, external
});

// Usage
activeConnections.set({ service: 'webhook' }, 42);
queueDepth.inc({ queue_name: 'orders', priority: 'high' }); // Increment
queueDepth.dec({ queue_name: 'orders', priority: 'high' }); // Decrement
```

### Histogram - Distribution of Values
```typescript
import { Histogram } from 'prom-client';

// Define histograms with buckets
const httpRequestDuration = new Histogram({
  name: 'http_request_duration_seconds',
  help: 'Duration of HTTP requests in seconds',
  labelNames: ['method', 'route', 'status_code'],
  buckets: [0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 1, 3, 5, 7, 10], // in seconds
});

const databaseQueryDuration = new Histogram({
  name: 'db_query_duration_seconds',
  help: 'Duration of database queries in seconds',
  labelNames: ['operation', 'table'],
  buckets: [0.001, 0.005, 0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.5, 1, 5],
});

// Usage with timer
const end = httpRequestDuration.startTimer({ 
  method: 'GET', 
  route: '/api/users' 
});
// ... do work ...
end({ status_code: '200' }); // Automatically records duration
```

### Summary - Percentiles Over Time Window
```typescript
import { Summary } from 'prom-client';

const apiLatency = new Summary({
  name: 'api_latency_seconds',
  help: 'API latency in seconds',
  labelNames: ['endpoint'],
  percentiles: [0.5, 0.9, 0.95, 0.99], // Calculate these percentiles
  maxAgeSeconds: 600, // 10-minute sliding window
  ageBuckets: 5, // Number of buckets for sliding window
});

// Usage
apiLatency.observe({ endpoint: '/api/orders' }, 0.123);
```

## 🔴 RED Metrics (Request-Oriented)

### Rate - Requests Per Second
```typescript
class REDMetrics {
  private requestRate = new Counter({
    name: 'http_requests_total',
    help: 'Total HTTP requests',
    labelNames: ['method', 'endpoint', 'service'],
  });

  recordRequest(method: string, endpoint: string) {
    this.requestRate.inc({
      method,
      endpoint,
      service: process.env.SERVICE_NAME,
    });
  }
}
```

### Errors - Error Rate
```typescript
private errorRate = new Counter({
  name: 'http_errors_total',
  help: 'Total HTTP errors',
  labelNames: ['method', 'endpoint', 'status_code', 'error_type'],
});

recordError(method: string, endpoint: string, statusCode: number, error?: Error) {
  this.errorRate.inc({
    method,
    endpoint,
    status_code: statusCode.toString(),
    error_type: error?.name || 'unknown',
  });
}
```

### Duration - Request Latency
```typescript
private requestDuration = new Histogram({
  name: 'http_request_duration_seconds',
  help: 'HTTP request duration in seconds',
  labelNames: ['method', 'endpoint', 'status_code'],
  buckets: [0.005, 0.01, 0.025, 0.05, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 1, 2.5, 5, 10],
});

// Express middleware
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  const timer = this.requestDuration.startTimer({
    method: req.method,
    endpoint: req.route?.path || req.path,
  });

  res.on('finish', () => {
    timer({ status_code: res.statusCode.toString() });
  });

  next();
});
```

## 🔧 USE Metrics (Resource-Oriented)

### Utilization - Average Resource Use
```typescript
class USEMetrics {
  private cpuUtilization = new Gauge({
    name: 'cpu_utilization_ratio',
    help: 'CPU utilization from 0 to 1',
    labelNames: ['service'],
  });

  private memoryUtilization = new Gauge({
    name: 'memory_utilization_ratio',
    help: 'Memory utilization from 0 to 1',
    labelNames: ['service', 'type'],
  });

  collectResourceMetrics() {
    // CPU utilization
    const cpuUsage = process.cpuUsage();
    const cpuPercent = (cpuUsage.user + cpuUsage.system) / 1000000; // Convert to seconds
    this.cpuUtilization.set({ service: process.env.SERVICE_NAME }, cpuPercent);

    // Memory utilization
    const memUsage = process.memoryUsage();
    this.memoryUtilization.set(
      { service: process.env.SERVICE_NAME, type: 'heap' },
      memUsage.heapUsed / memUsage.heapTotal
    );
    this.memoryUtilization.set(
      { service: process.env.SERVICE_NAME, type: 'rss' },
      memUsage.rss / os.totalmem()
    );
  }
}
```

### Saturation - Queue Depth, Thread Pool Usage
```typescript
private queueSaturation = new Gauge({
  name: 'queue_saturation_ratio',
  help: 'Queue saturation from 0 to 1',
  labelNames: ['queue_name'],
});

private threadPoolSaturation = new Gauge({
  name: 'thread_pool_saturation_ratio',
  help: 'Thread pool saturation from 0 to 1',
  labelNames: ['pool_name'],
});

recordQueueMetrics(queueName: string, currentSize: number, maxSize: number) {
  this.queueSaturation.set(
    { queue_name: queueName },
    currentSize / maxSize
  );
}
```

### Errors - Resource Errors
```typescript
private resourceErrors = new Counter({
  name: 'resource_errors_total',
  help: 'Total resource errors',
  labelNames: ['resource_type', 'error_type'],
});

recordResourceError(resourceType: string, errorType: string) {
  this.resourceErrors.inc({
    resource_type: resourceType, // 'database', 'cache', 'queue'
    error_type: errorType, // 'timeout', 'connection_refused', 'pool_exhausted'
  });
}
```

