## ✅ Testing Metrics

```typescript
import { register } from 'prom-client';

describe('Metrics', () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    register.clear();
  });

  it('should increment request counter', async () => {
    const metrics = new REDMetrics();
    
    metrics.recordRequest('GET', '/api/users');
    metrics.recordRequest('GET', '/api/users');
    
    const metricsText = await register.metrics();
    expect(metricsText).toContain('http_requests_total{method="GET",endpoint="/api/users"} 2');
  });

  it('should record request duration', async () => {
    const metrics = new REDMetrics();
    
    const timer = metrics.startTimer('GET', '/api/users');
    await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 100));
    timer({ status_code: '200' });
    
    const metricsText = await register.metrics();
    expect(metricsText).toContain('http_request_duration_seconds_bucket');
  });
});
```

## 🚨 Anti-Patterns

```typescript
// ❌ BAD: High cardinality labels
httpRequestsTotal.inc({ 
  user_id: userId, // Millions of unique values!
  timestamp: Date.now() // Infinite cardinality!
});

// ❌ BAD: Not using labels
const getUsersTotal = new Counter({ name: 'get_users_total' });
const postUsersTotal = new Counter({ name: 'post_users_total' });

// ❌ BAD: Wrong metric type
const requestCount = new Gauge({ // Should be Counter!
  name: 'request_count'
});

// ✅ GOOD: Proper labels and types
const httpRequests = new Counter({
  name: 'http_requests_total',
  labelNames: ['method', 'endpoint', 'status_code'],
});
```

## 📊 Success Metrics for Metrics (Meta!)

- **Metric Coverage**: 100% of services expose /metrics
- **Scrape Success Rate**: > 99.9%
- **Metric Cardinality**: < 10,000 unique series per service
- **Query Performance**: P95 < 1 second
- **Dashboard Load Time**: < 3 seconds
- **Alert Evaluation Time**: < 10 seconds

